DRESSING‚Å†
4 tablespoons olive oil‚Å†
2 tablespoons honey‚Å†
1 teaspoon salt‚Å†
¬Ω teaspoon pepper‚Å†
4 tablespoons lime juice‚Å†
‚Å†
Preparation‚Å†
In a medium bowl, combine all the ingredients for the chicken marinade.‚Å†
Toss in the chicken thighs and marinate for at least one hour.‚Å†
In a cast-iron skillet, cook chicken on high heat until there is a nice sear on the surface of the chicken, and the inside is no longer pink. Roughly four minutes each side. Set chicken aside.‚Å†
Place chopped lettuce, tomatoes, red onion, and avocados in a large salad bowl.‚Å†
Slice cooked chicken thighs and add to the salad bowl.‚Å†
In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients for the dressing. Mix well.‚Å†
Toss the salad with the dressing and serve immediately.‚Å†
Enjoy!‚Å†

Palak  1 bunch

Lemon 1 large  squeezed

Grind all ingredients.

Crispy fried Shrimp üç§üç§üç§ In a bowl add 1b shrimp with 1/2 cup all purpose flour, 1/2 cup corn starch, 2 tbsp seasoning sauce (or soy sauce), black pepper, garlic powder, 1 beaten egg and mix well. Add 3/4 cup of Panko bread crumbs and mix well. If you find that the shrimp stick together don't worry about it.
Deep fry. 
I didn't have Sweet chili sauce on hand so I came up with my own sauce.

For the sauce you need

1 tsp chili flakes, 1 tbsp maple syrup,1 tbsp ketchup, 1 tbsp sugar and 1 tbsp vinegar. 
Mix well! Enjoy! :

description:
Chicken Tray Bake - Chicken & Veggies with Garlic & Thyme 
When it‚Äôs a mini celebration of sorts and you want to eat something yummy yet not spend the day in the kitchen - Chicken Tray Bake is the solution. 
I marinated the chicken in the morning and let it freeze in my fridge. Prepped the veggies while the oven preheated and chucked it in the oven about 45mins before dinner time. 
I marinated the skinless chicken legs and the veggies (potatoes, carrots, onions and capsicum) in olive oil, thyme, garlic cloves, paprika, ground pepper and salt. I placed the chicken on the veggies and topped with coriander leaves (couldn‚Äôt find parsley) and cooked it in the oven for about 40mins till the juices ran clear, the veggies were soft and roasted and had absorbed all the chicken juices and the chicken had charred well. Served with toasted local bread. 
This was also a big portion for 2 persons so the extra will be shredded chicken and veggies in a sandwich for breakfast or a side for lunch depending on our mood tomorrow morning. .

description:
Last week, I made these yumilicious Peri Bites, over the ‚Äòfarmaish‚Äô of my dear husband! üòä
The recipe is pretty simple, you could either use green chilis or Jalape√±os, depending upon your spice level üå∂ I have served them hot, with French dipping sauce.
.
Recipeüëá
.
.
.
.
.
Ingredients:
-Chicken small cubes 1 lb
-Nando‚Äôs hot peri-peri sauce 3 tbsp
-Salt to taste üßÇ
-Oil 1 tbsp
-Grated cheese - cheddar and mozzarella 3 tbsp each
-Milk 1 cup
-Jalape√±os 10
-Eggs 2 (for coating) -Bread crumbs 1 cup (for coating)
.
Method:
-Cook chicken with oil, peri-peri sauce and salt in a frying pan
-Take milk in a sauce pan and add cheese to it; mix well until the texture becomes nice and smooth
-Using a knife, carefully make a cut perpendicular to the base of Jalape√±os and remove the seeds - must wear the gloves!!
-Insert 1-2 chicken pieces into each chili followed by a small quantity of the cheese sauce
-Now whisk 2 eggs in a bowl; coat each Jalape√±o in eggs, followed by rolling them in bread crumbs
-Deep fry in hot oil until they have a nice golden coat
.

Bersihkan ikan cencaru dan kelar di bahagian belakang ikan untuk dijadikan poket.
.
Kisar cili merah, bawang merah, bawang putih dan serai sehingga halus.
.
Tumiskan bahan-bahan yang telah dikisar dengan sedikit minyak.
.
Tumis sehingga bahan-bahana tersebut agak garing. Tambahkan garam dan gula.
.
Kemudian masukkan kelapa parut dan perahan air limau.
.
Gaul semuanya sehingga sebati.
.
Sumbatkan sambal kelapa ke dalam poket ikan. Pastikan padat supaya sambal kelapa tak terkeluar ketika dibakar.
.
Bakar ikan lebih kurang 5 minit setiap bahagian. Aku tak suka kalau ikan bakar kering sangat.
.
Sedia untuk dihidangkan!
.
Boleh dihidangkan begitu sahaja atau kalau korang suka makan dengan air asam pun ok.
.
Selamat mencuba.

description:
Hi friends üòç Salaam to all .Chicken fillets are the heart of chicken shawarma .This is the easiest part in preparing shawarma rolls coz we are going to  just marinate and fry . Let's go to recipe :
CHICKEN MARINATION :
CHICKEN - 250 GRAMS
PEPPER - 1/4 TSP
CHILLI POWDER - 1/4 TSP
GARLIC MINCED- 1 TBSP
CUMIN POWDER - 1/2 TSP
TANDOORI CHICKEN MASALA - 1 TSP
LEMON JUICE - 1 TSP
CINNAMON POWDER - 1/8 TSP
VIRGIN OLIVE OIL - 3 TBSP( 1TBSP GOES FOR MARINATION)
SALT TO TASTE
SHAWARMA ROLL:
ONION FINELY CHOPPED -1/8  CUP
CABBAGE FINELY CHOPPED -1/8 CUP
JULIENNED CARROTS - 1/4 CUP
JULIENNED CAPSICUM -1/4 CUP
JULIENNED TOMATOES -1/4 CUP
ONION SLICED -1/4 CUP
METHOD:
*First slice the boneless chicken in to strips then marinate with the above ingredients .
* Keep aside for 2 hours or refrigerate it .
*Heat oil in skillet, keep in medium flame ,then add the marinated chicken pieces and cook by flipping its sides till they turn brown.If need add more oil while frying it.
* Once the chicken frying part is over ,move on to the shawarma assembling process.
* Mix the finely chopped onion,cabbage to the shawarma sauce .It will  add a crunchiness to sauce (Optional)
*Place a pita bread in a rolling board ,apply 1TBSP of sauce and spread over it ,put chicken fillets ,julienned vegetables and roll it up.
* If u want more saucy add one more layer of sauce above julienned vegetables.
Yayyy!!! Juicy Chicken Shawarma roll is  ready üòãüòã
TIP:
*If u want u can avoid adding julienned vegetables its purely optional
Friends do try tis recipe and comment me how it turned out ‚ò∫

CONGEE W/ SNAPPER .
.
‚Ä¢ Chilli & Ginger Snapper ‚Ä¢ Chinese-style Congee ‚Ä¢ Mushrooms ‚Ä¢ Ginger ‚Ä¢ Garlic ‚Ä¢ Chilli ‚Ä¢ Spring Onion ‚Ä¢ Homemade Veggie Stock ‚Ä¢ .
.
I first tried this in Cambodia and since then Congee has forever been my fave and I‚Äôve always wanted to try make it. You‚Äôre meant to use Jasmine rice as I thinks it creates a better starchy soup but I used what I had. .
. 
Fry all the flavours (garlic, ginger, mushroom, chilli), set half aside for garnish and add rice to the other half. Cover rice with stock and leave to boil for an hour and a half until you get a thick soup - adding more stock if needed and seasoning where necessary. For the snapper combine ginger, garlic, chilli paste, lime juice and butter - bang inside and on top of the fish and put at 190 for 20 mins. When the rice soup is finished add an egg and fold through, this gives you silky little threads. GALLETAS PICANTES DE CHOCOLATE
__
 para hacerlas necesitan: 
__
*1 huevo *1/4 de manteca vegetal o mantequilla *1/3 de az√∫car *1 cucharada de miel *1 cucharadita de polvo para hornear *1/4 de cacao en polvo*un poco de vainilla* 1/2 cucharadita de canela*media taza de harina de arroz*1/4 de taza de almid√≥n de ma√≠z(Maizena)*Una pizca de sal*1/4 de cucharadita de pimienta cayena.(opcional:az√∫car pulverizada)

Para elaborarlas primero debemos precalentar el horno a 160 C¬∞;colocar en un recipiente el huevo, la manteca(o mantequilla), el az√∫car, la miel, la vainilla y la pizca de sal; seguido de esto procedemos a batir la mezcla ya sea de forma manual o con una batidora autom√°tica hasta que observemos que la manteca se ha dispersado por toda la mezcla.

En un recipiente a parte mezclamos las harinas con la canela y el polvo para hornear. Agregamos el 1/4 de taza de cacao a la mezcla que hicimos anteriormente y una vez que est√° tome color agregamos la mezcla de harinas que usamos

Cuando est√° este integrada deber√≠a quedar una masa manejable, de haber quedado muy suave les recomiendo llevar la masa a su refrigerador y dejar all√≠ por 10 minutos.

Puede proceder a armarlas de dos formas.

1-Armar las galletas a mano formando bolitas y d√°ndoles forma despu√©s.

2.o bien puede extender la mass sobre una superficie limpia previamente espolvoreada con un poco de harina, y aplanar con un rodillo hasta q tenga el grosor deseado y usar el molde de galletas de su preferencia.

Despu√©s de haber armado y dispuesto las galletas sobre una bandeja, las llevamos al horno por 13 minutos; retiramos del horno,las dejamos enfriar y listo tendr√°n una deliciosa merienda lista para disfrutar con la familia o amigos(Para decorar puede espolvorear az√∫car pulverizada sobre est√°s una vez que est√°s se hayan enfriado)

RECIPE 
Dough for steamed buns/ pau
Pau wheat flour  500g
Instant yeast  8-10g
Warm water  150-200ml
Sugar  1-2 table spoon 
Salt  A bit (optionalÔºâ

For the filling
Depends on what do you like (Char Siu/ pork, chicken, red bean, grated coconut and so on)

INSTRUCTIONS 
1. Prepare ingredients to make the skin of the pau or steamed buns.
2. First, place the pau wheat flour into a mixing bowl.
3. Place the warm water into a glass and add in yeast, sugar and salt, stir well.
4. Combine the yeast mixture with pau wheat flour and knead until the dough is soft, smooth, elastic and does not stick to the sides of the mixing bowl or to your fingers.
5. Cover with a piece of wet cloth and leave to prove until it has doubled its size. I leave it for 45 minutes.
6. Punch down dough to release the air inside, briefly knead again till all is evenly distributed. And you have the basic dough for making pau (buns).
7. Divide the smooth dough in half. Roll into long cylindrical shapes.
8. Cut the dough and shape into balls.
9. Roll each ball into a flat circle with a small rolling pin.
10. Do the same for the rest of the round balls.
11. Have ready the savory any fillings prepared earlier.
12. Spoon in filling into each flattened dough.
13. Gather the edges of the flat dough together.
14. Shape it into pleated pau (bun).
15. Place the pleated pau onto cut parchment or greaseproof paper.
16. Place the pleated pau (buns) onto steaming tray or plate (with holes to allow steam to pass).
17. Leave to prove until double in size, about 15 - 20 minutes.
18. When about time to steam the buns, boil some water in a wok or steamer.
19. Place the buns on steaming tray into the wok.
20. Cover and steam over medium heat for 15 minutes.
21. Transfer steamed buns onto rack to cool before serving. Good lucküòÑ

This week we made Chicken Francese and it turned out pretty good! Definitely recommend as a great weeknight dinner üòã

Ingredients:
Chicken:
1/2 cup all-purpose flour.
1 tsp salt or to taste.
1/2 tsp pepper freshly ground, or to taste.
3 large eggs.
1/4 cup vegetable oil.
4 chicken breasts boneless and skinless, thin sliced. -

Sauce.
1 large lemon sliced into thin rounds, seeds removed.
1 cup chicken broth low sodium.
1/2 cup white wine dry.
1 tbsp lemon juice freshly squeezed.
1 tbsp all-purpose flour.
2 tbsp butter unsalted.
2 tbsp parsley chopped, for garnish. -

Instructions:
1. Prepare the flour and eggs: In a shallow plate, add the 1/2 cup of flour, 1 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp of pepper. Whisk to combine. In another shallow plate or bowl whisk the eggs.
2. Dredge the cutlets in the flour mixture, fully coating both sides and shaking off any excess. Next, coat them in the egg mixture.
3. Heat the oil in a large 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat until simmering. Add 3 or 4 pieces of chicken to the skillet (or as many as you can fit). Cook until lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer the chicken to a paper towel-lined plate. Repeat with remaining chicken.
4. Make the sauce: Clean the skillet of any excess oil, then add the lemon slices and cook until fragrant and slightly charred, about 30 seconds per side. Add the butter to the skillet and melt it. Whisk in the flour and cook for 30 seconds to cook off the flour taste. Whisk in the wine, broth, lemon juice, and remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt and season with pepper. Simmer until slightly reduced, about 2 minutes.
5. Finish the dish: Return the chicken to the skillet and cook until for another 3 to 4 minutes. Garnish with the parsley before serving.
-

Tidak terasa sudah dipenghujung Ramadhan. Rasanya cepat sekali Ramadhan meninggalkan kita. Semoga ibadah kita semua diterima oleh-Nya. Aamiin. 
Salah satu takjil favorit saya adalah cendol, sampai saat ini saya suka nyetok tepung cendol dirumah. Jadi kita tinggal memasak dan mencetak saja adonannya. Dulu saya beli alat yang satu paket dengan tepungnya disalah satu TBK di Surabaya. Sebenarnya beberapa kali pernah mencoba eksperimen membuat sendiri adonan cendolnya tapi hasilnya kurang maksimal. Lain kali saya akan coba membuat kembali dan berbagi resepnya kepada teman-teman ya, hehe. 
Nahh.. untuk menambah nilai gizi kali ini saya menambahkan kacang merah seperti permintaan adik saya. Kacang merah kaya akan berbagai nutrisi seperti serat, antioksidan, protein, asam folat, zat besi dan lain sebagainya. Kacang merah ini memiliki indeks glikemik yang rendah sehingga sangat baik untuk penderita diabetes. 
Yukk buat sendiri cendol dirumah. Selamat mencoba teman-teman.. Es Cendol Kacang Merah

Bahan :
1 sachet Tepung cendol siap pakai 
100 gram Nangka, potong dadu kecil
500 ml Santan kental, rebus dengan daun pandan dan sedikit garam
250 gram Gula merah, rebus dengan sedikit air dan daun pandan
Es batu secukupnya

200 gram Kacang merah, rendam semalaman
75 gram Gula kelapa
Air secukupnya
Daun pandan 
Cara membuat :
1. Siapkan panci rebus kacang merah bersama gula kelapa dan daun pandan hingga lunak. Sisihkan.
2. Buat adonan cendol sesuai instruksi pada kemasan. Lalu cetak menggunakan Catalan cendol pada air es. Sisihkan.

description:
PUMPKIN MUFFINSü§§ü§§
{gluten free + dairy free + refined sugar free + lowfodmap}
‚†Ä
this is seriously one of the best recipes i‚Äôve ever made. muffin texture is so fluffy & so moist it‚Äôs unreal that they‚Äôre gf, df & full of healthier ingredients. I promise u won‚Äôt be disappointedü§©
‚†Ä
_________________________________
‚úèÔ∏èRecipe: about 12 muffins
>INGREDIENTS
* 1 1/2 c @bobsredmill 1-to-1 gf flour
* 1 tsp baking powder
* 1 tsp baking soda
* 1/2 tsp salt
* 2.5 tsp @mccormickspice cinnamon
* 2 @vitalfarms eggs
* 1/4 c @thefreshmarket 100% maple syrup
* 1/2 c @carringtonfarms coconut oil
* 1/2 can (1 c) @traderjoes canned pumpkin
* sweetener (optional but recommended if you like sweetness. I used 1/2 tsp of stevia extract powder which was = to 1/4 c sugar for reference, I would do at least 1 tsp if u want it more like dessert!)
‚†Ä
>DIRECTIONS
-Preheat oven to 350F.
-Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt & cinnamon.
-In separate large bowl, beat eggs until combined.
-While beating, add in oil & maple syrup.
-With mixer at low speed, add sifted dry ingredients alternatively with pumpkin, begin & end this with dry ingredients. Beat until smooth between each addition.
-Pour into lightly greased muffin tin (about 12 muffins). I topped mine with a few walnuts.
-Bake for 20-25 minutes.
enjoyyyy‚ú®

description:
Once in a while I used to get lunch from this Hawaiian Korean fusion restaurant close to my work. My go to was their kimchi fried rice with chicken, and a sunny side up egg! I was craving that for soooo long, and finally decided to give it a try. I‚Äôm pleasantly surprised how delicious this turned out to be! And also looks gorgeous! Probably not the most authentic, but here‚Äôs the recipe, and it barely took 30 minutes to make:
1. Season 1lb of shrimp with salt, a pinch of turmeric and 1tsp of ground black pepper
2. Heat 1tbsp of oil in a deep pan or wok, cook the shrimp for about 2 minutes and set aside
3. In the same pan, add another 1tbsp of oil, and saute 1cup of chopped onions, 1tbsp of minced garlic. 
4. Once thoroughly cooked, add 1 cup of drained kimchi and 1tbsp of gochujang paste, cook for about 2-3 minutes.
5. Add the kimchi juice, 2tsps of soy sauce and 2tsps of fish sauce and cook for another 1 minute.
6. Add 2 cups of cooked day-old rice, and mix really well. Cook for 3-4 minutes
7. Move all the rice to a side, and crack 2 eggs on the other side, cook until it‚Äôs set and season with salt and pepper. Scramble the eggs and combine with the rice really well.
8. Add the cooked shrimp at this point and cook for a minute.
9. Squeeze half a lemon and throw in some chopped scallions and give it a good mix.
10. Serve with a sunny side up egg!

description:
#Repost from @helenysm_ (@repost_media_app)
Frozen Pork Noodles!
Praktis dan nikmat buat sarapan.

Buat kalian yang suka bingung, mau sarapan apa, sementara sekarang ribet beli-beli di luar. Mending stok aja Frozen Noodles di rumah, jadinya kapanpun bisa nge-yamien.

Bakmi Asia punya aneka macam Frozen Pork Noodles, dengan beberapa pilihan homemade noodle seperti: mie biasa dan mie gepeng, ada juga mie hijau yang terbuat dari poleng/caisim. Bisa pilih juga  mau pakai baso atau pangsit. Pokoknya sesuai selera masing-masing deh.

Frozen Pork Noodles ini sudah komplit termasuk topping babi kecap cincang, ayam suwir, bawang goreng dan sambal. Pokoknya tinggal dimasak bentar, langsung enak deh.

Yuk borong buat stok #dirumahaja.

Bakmi Asia

Savoury Vegan Bowl ü•ëü•ó
‚óÜIngredients‚óÜ
‚óèolive oil
‚óèa bunch of cherry tomatoes on the vine
‚óè250 g / 9 oz cooked and cooled small potatoes, halved
‚óè salt to taste
‚óè black pepper, to taste
‚óè100 g / 3.5 oz baby spinach
‚óè 1 large shallot, finely diced
‚óè 1 garlic clove, finely diced
‚óè300 g / 10.5 oz silken firm tofu (I use¬†Clearspring)
‚óè¬º tsp turmeric, adjust to taste
‚óè¬º tsp¬†black salt¬†(has eggy taste), adjust to taste
‚óè¬Ω ripe avocado, cut in half

Methods:
‚óè Brush tomatoes with a little oil (keeping them on the vine if you can) and place them on a small baking tray. Stick them under a grill / broiler for 5-10 minutes, until their skins burst and the tops char a little. Season and set aside. ‚óè Heat up 2 tsp of olive oil on a small frying pan. Place cold potatoes, cut side down on the hot oil and allow them to fry gently until nicely browned. Season with salt and pepper. ‚óè Place spinach on another pan with a splash of water. Allow the spinach to wilt using gentle heat. Move it around the pan with a pair of tongs. Season and lift wilted spinach out of the pan, draining any excess water away. ‚óè Heat up a tablespoon of oil in a pan (I reused the one I used to wilt the spinach) and fry diced shallot and garlic on a very gentle heat. ‚óèOnce shallot is translucent and garlic fragrant (but not browned), add the drained tofu. Smash it a little with the back of a spoon. Season with turmeric, black salt (it will give it eggy taste) and pepper. ‚óè Divide all the elements (including the avocado) between two bowls and drizzle with extra olive oil if needed.

¬Ω teaspoon pepper‚Å†
4 tablespoons lime juice‚Å†
‚Å†
Preparation‚Å†
In a medium bowl, combine all the ingredients for the chicken marinade.‚Å†
Toss in the chicken thighs and marinate for at least one hour.‚Å†
In a cast-iron skillet, cook chicken on high heat until there is a nice sear on the surface of the chicken, and the inside is no longer pink. Roughly four minutes each side. Set chicken aside.‚Å†
Place chopped lettuce, tomatoes, red onion, and avocados in a large salad bowl.‚Å†
Slice cooked chicken thighs and add to the salad bowl.‚Å†
In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients for the dressing. Mix well.‚Å†
Toss the salad with the dressing and serve immediately.‚Å†
Enjoy!‚Å†

SHRIMP PESTO BOWLüç§üç§
{gluten & dairy free + lowfodmap}
‚†Ä
made the best shrimp bowl using my homemade pesto recipe. highly recommend for anyone looking for a dairy free pesto it‚Äôs super easy & tastes amazingü§ó
‚†Ä
>dEATS
* @thefreshmarket shrimp
* @traderjoes cherry tomatoes
* @thefreshmarket zucchini noodles
* @fodyfoods garlic olive oil
* @rachelpaulsfood italian seasoning
* spoonful of my homemade pestoüëáüèº
‚†Ä
________________________________________
‚úèÔ∏èPesto Recipe: makes a few servings
>INGREDIENTS
* 1/2 c basil
* 1/2 c spinach (or another green)
* 1/4 c arugula
* 1/2 c pine nuts
* 3 tbsp lemon juice
* 3 tbsp nutritional yeast
* 1/4 c olive oil
* lots of salt & pepper as needed
‚†Ä
>DIRECTIONS
-Place all ingredients in food processor & blend until combined. Can taste it & add more of anything if needed.
** I like to make this whole batch then freeze it for future meals. If you have an ice cube tray you can make ice cubes with this then keep in a freezer bag & take out cubes to melt on pan when needed; super easy! **
‚ú®enjoyyyy

description:
Frozen Pork Noodles!
Praktis dan nikmat buat sarapan.

Buat kalian yang suka bingung, mau sarapan apa, sementara sekarang ribet beli-beli di luar. Mending stok aja Frozen Noodles di rumah, jadinya kapanpun bisa nge-yamien.

Bakmi Asia punya aneka macam Frozen Pork Noodles, dengan beberapa pilihan homemade noodle seperti: mie biasa dan mie gepeng, ada juga mie hijau yang terbuat dari poleng/caisim. Bisa pilih juga  mau pakai baso atau pangsit. Pokoknya sesuai selera masing-masing deh.

Frozen Pork Noodles ini sudah komplit termasuk topping babi kecap cincang, ayam suwir, bawang goreng dan sambal. Pokoknya tinggal dimasak bentar, langsung enak deh.

Yuk borong buat stok #dirumahaja.

Bakmi Asia

description:
Peshwa¬†Baji Rao I, prime minister to¬†Chattrapati Shahu, laid the ceremonial foundation of his own residence on Saturday, 10 January 1730. It was named¬†Shaniwarwadafrom the Marathi words¬†Shaniwar¬†(Saturday) and¬†Wada¬†(a general term for any residence complex).¬†Teak¬†was imported from the jungles of¬†Junnar, stone was brought from the nearby quarries of¬†Chinchwad, and¬†Lime (mineral)was brought from the lime-belts of¬†Jejuri. Shaniwarwada was completed in 1732, at a total cost of Rs. 16,110, a very large sum at that time.

The opening ceremony was performed according to religious customs, on 22 January 1732, another Saturday chosen for being a particularly auspicious day.

Later the Peshwas made several additions, including the fortification walls, with bastions and gates; court halls and other buildings; fountains and reservoirs. Currently, the perimeter fortification wall has five gateways and nine bastion towers, enclosing a garden complex with the foundations of the original buildings. It is situated near the¬†Mula-Mutha River, in¬†Kasba Peth.

description:
Spike Speigel - from Cowboy Bebop - arguably the best character in Anime history - voiced by the legendary @blumspew who had a birthday the other day - Happy belated birthday sir. I'm excited to see the live-action series coming to Netflix and I'm especially excited to see what @johnthecho does with the role of Spike.

The show itself has been heavily influential on my life - I first saw shortly after my parents' divorce and even though I didn't know it at the time - it's a show about letting go. It also genre hops with each episode and with the music, plus the animation is just top-notch. It's timeless, it's complete and it all started from a toy spaceship contract with Bandai and it's very gifted Director @shinichiro_watanabe

Anywho this was a sharpie doodle - and I took it into photoshop for a really basic coloring session. Enjoy.

description:
MATI GAYA KELAMAAN WFH

Anak-anak saya termasuk dalam kategori pahlawan dimasa Pandemi ini.. Kerjaannya di dominasi oleh aktivitas "rebahan." Memang kadang ada kuliah/kelas online dan olahraga-diet. Tapi utamanya tetap saja rebahan.

Saking sudah lamanya WFH/SFH, mereka mulai mati gaya karena tidak punya foto baru untuk di upload di media sosial mereka. Makanya hari ini anak wedok tiba-tiba masuk kamar saya saat saya sedang ngobrol sama Bojo dan bilang minta tolong fotoin dan juga sudah dandan. Ini berarti agak serius untuk buat foto baru. Dapar order motret anak wedok, bapaknya age-age gresek-gresek ambil camera, langsung mangkat menyang... Anak millenials kalau berpose selalu punya gaya standar. Lidah nya melet üòÇ... Ini tentu saja diluar selera fotografi bapaknya. Makanya bapaknya nunggu momen saat anak wedok mbenerin pose, langsung jepret, candid. Jadinya adalah foto ini... Bapaknya happy melihat hasilnya. Setelah foto di share, anak wedok juga happy karena dalam sejam di upload, sudah ada ratusan yang nge-like.

Melihat hasil foto anak wedok, Bojo saya jadi juga kepingin di foto. Tentu saja saya juga age-age mau motret bojo... Tapi bojo ternyata punya target pra-kondisi... "Aku di foto ya... Tapi nanti kalau sudah kurus..." Wah lha kalau prakondisi yang di syaratkan itu adalah "kurus", ya nggak akan kelakon fotonya... üòÇüòÇüòÇ #kurusiturelatif

description:
Constant Variable : 136/366 Days Portrait 
Title: Bi-Lingual
15-05-2020
Pen on paper 11"x14"
The Jain philosophical doctrine 'Anekantvada' forms the basis of my interdisciplinary practice. The doctrine states that all entities have three aspects: substance (dravya), quality (guna) and mode (paryaya), and each of them is constantly undergoing transformation and modification. These elements make perception of reality difficult to assess from one one point of view. Each view-point yields, different conclusion. The nature of reality is expressed completely none of them but by all of them together. 
The only constant in my life for past 10 years has been @jeysushil . This art project titled- 'Constant Variable' is an ambitious act of analysing one subject over 366 days' through as many portraits.

description:
Mindfulness is our natural quality but most of us have lost it in our busy lives which usually is on autopilot mode. In simple words mindfulness can also be explained as simply trying to bring our attention to the present moment and that too without judgement. It can be practiced either as a form of mindfulness meditation or by focusing on simple everyday activities like eating or breathing. The key word is 'without any Judgement.' We have to try to quieten the inner critic in our heads while paying attention and if we start to judge, then we make a mental note of it and let it pass. It's about living in the moment, being present and returning to the present moment again and again. Mindfulness has a lot of scientifically proven benefits which I will share in my next post. Stay safe everyone and Happy Weekend..

description:
Jumping Frogs

The Story:

A group of frogs was hopping through the forest when two of them accidentally hopped into a deep pit. The other frogs stood around the pit, and, seeing how deep it was, they told the two frogs that they couldn‚Äôt help them‚Äìthere was no hope.

However, fighting for their lives, the two frogs ignored the others and started to try jumping out of the pit.

The frogs at the top continued to tell the frogs in the pit to give up, as there was no way they would be able to jump out.

After trying over and over, one of the frogs listened to the others and gave up, accepting his fate and falling to his death. But the other frog continued to jump with all of his might. The crowd of frogs yelled down the pit for the frog to just stop‚Äìhe wouldn‚Äôt make it.

But the frog jumped even harder and persisted until he finally got out. Upon reaching the top, the other frogs said, ‚ÄúWe thought there was no way any frog could jump that high‚Äìcouldn‚Äôt you hear us?‚Äù The frog then signaled to the others that he was deaf, and he thought that the frogs standing around the pit were encouraging him the whole time.

The Moral:

Others‚Äô words can greatly impact your attitude and actions. Ignore the naysayers. Only engage with those¬†who encourage you¬†and believe in your ability to succeed. Furthermore, think about what you say to people before speaking so you can make sure what you‚Äôre saying is supportive. Your support (or lack thereof) could make the difference between success and failure .
